1. Explain what a token is used for.

    A token is used for issuing authentication when users input the correct information.

2. What steps can you take in your web apps to keep your data secure?

    The key step will be requiring users to sign in to have a token before viewing the data.

3. Describe how web servers work.

    Web server serve users by sending out users' requested web pages data.

4. Which HTTP methods can be mapped to the CRUD acronym that we use when interfacing with APIs/Servers.

     C - Create that goes with post request.
     R - Read that goes with get request.
     U - Update that goes with put request.
     D - Delete that goes with delete request.
